cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with joint modeling of language and vision, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The focus is on multimodal retrieval, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The paper also introduces a new model selection method and a new sentence embedding technique, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
